WEBVTT

00:27.810 --> 00:28.671
Welcome, Church.

00:29.171 --> 00:34.197
I'm Mike Davis, and I'm so glad that you're here today to worship with us.

00:34.878 --> 00:44.068
You know, it was over one year that my brother called me from Jamaica and said, listen, Mike, that is in the hospital and he suffered a stroke.

00:44.629 --> 00:46.070
I was very devastated.

00:46.731 --> 00:48.793
I was so in despair, anxious.

00:49.594 --> 00:50.735
I didn't know what to do.

00:51.356 --> 00:56.882
But then I was reminded of a scripture, Psalms 34, that says,

00:57.218 --> 00:59.481
I will bless the Lord at all times.

00:59.942 --> 01:02.926
His praise shall continually be in my mouth.

01:03.507 --> 01:06.330
My soul shall make a boast in the Lord.

01:06.350 --> 01:10.095
The humble shall hear of it and be glad.

01:10.856 --> 01:17.546
But then the scripture transitioned and it said, O magnify the Lord with me.

01:17.566 --> 01:21.130
And let us exalt his name together.

01:21.150 --> 01:26.738
I sought the Lord and he heard me and delivered me from all my fear.

01:27.842 --> 01:30.806
I was so comforted in those words.

01:31.427 --> 01:34.831
I began to sing and I began to meditate on that.

01:35.813 --> 01:37.194
You know what that brought to me?

01:37.235 --> 01:49.030
It brought a hopeful anticipation that something good would happen if I would just focus on worshiping God.

01:49.851 --> 01:50.773
Are you there today?

01:50.793 --> 01:54.297
Are you in trouble, despair, frustration?

01:54.357 --> 01:57.842
You do not know where to turn on what to do.

01:58.466 --> 02:02.677
Well friends, God is here with us.

02:03.799 --> 02:09.554
Won't you join us today as we worship Him in spirit and in truth?

07:53.730 --> 08:01.373
You're the light that guides me through How's it on you?

08:04.041 --> 08:08.274
You are near to the broken, though we find the strength

08:30.658 --> 08:39.346
My soul lies around you You bring hope to the hope

09:28.610 --> 09:54.290
You're the love and won't let go Our eyes are on you We lift our eyes to You Where our hair comes from Our hope is found in You Jesus, Lord, of all we lift our eyes to You Exalted

10:37.858 --> 10:44.245
Jesus, Lord of all we lift our eyes to You.

10:44.265 --> 10:55.257
Exalted one.

10:55.277 --> 10:57.779
We lift our eyes to You.

10:57.799 --> 11:00.402
Where our hair comes from, our hope is found in You.

11:00.422 --> 11:06.689
Jesus, Lord of all we lift our eyes to You.

11:06.709 --> 11:07.730
Exalted one.

11:12.226 --> 11:13.043
This world...

15:48.578 --> 15:54.445
friends as we get ready to lean into a brand new series that we're calling rejuvenated.

15:55.065 --> 16:04.256
I thought it'd be a great time as we enter into a time of prayer to be reminded of one of God's greatest gifts that He's given to us and that's the gift of Sabbath.

16:04.896 --> 16:17.170
Every seven days God instructs us to take a breather and to position ourselves to receive refreshment from Him and from connecting with family and friends.

16:17.634 --> 16:32.448
Sabbath is this weekly reminder that we have physical, emotional, and spiritual limits in that it is good and proper to become more and more dependent on the power of Holy Spirit, to become less and less dependent on our own strength.

16:33.529 --> 16:39.535
I got a share there that I think that Sabbath is also a form of cultural resistance.

16:39.555 --> 16:47.122
That everything in our society declares that we need to produce more, to do more, to be more, and this production

16:47.234 --> 16:48.756
communicates our value.

16:49.636 --> 16:59.686
And Sabbath runs directly counter to this message that our worth does not lie in how much we produce, our worth rests solely with God.

17:00.687 --> 17:11.118
So friends, today I want to lead us in a prayer that helps to welcome us into a time of Sabbath to prepare our hearts to receive everything God wants to provide through this time together.

17:11.158 --> 17:15.282
So allow me to just pray this prayer over us today

17:15.490 --> 17:18.493
and allow these words to minister to your spirit.

17:20.496 --> 17:40.218
Lord of creation, create in us a new rhythm of life composed of hours that sustain rather than stress of days that deliver rather than destroy, of time that trickles rather than tackles.

17:41.279 --> 17:44.242
Lord of liberation by the rhythm of your truth

17:44.482 --> 17:54.537
Set us free from the bondage and baggage that break us, from the pharaohs and fellows who fail us, from the plans and pursuits that prey upon us.

17:55.599 --> 18:13.586
Lord of Resurrection, may we be raised into the rhythm of your new life, dead to deceitful calendars, dead to fleeting friend requests, dead to the empty piece of our accomplishments, to our packed full planners, we say, peace.

18:14.210 --> 18:17.595
To our over-caffeinated consciences, we say, cease.

18:18.536 --> 18:23.203
To our suffocating selves, Lord, we ask that you would grant release.

18:24.265 --> 18:28.932
Drowning in a sea of deadlines, we rest in you, our lifeline.

18:30.034 --> 18:36.844
By your ever-restful grace, allow us to enter your Sabbath rest as your Sabbath rest enters into us.

18:37.905 --> 18:43.794
In the name of our Creator, our Liberator, our Resurrection and Life, we pray,

18:44.642 --> 18:45.235
Amen.

19:32.418 --> 19:36.089
It was a hot summer day, a lot like the ones that we've been experiencing here lately.

19:36.511 --> 19:43.653
And my brother and sister and I and some cousins, we had been out working hard on the little ranch that I grew up in in the desert Southwest.

19:44.295 --> 19:45.298
Part of our

19:45.378 --> 19:52.669
every day experience during the summer was to take a dip in my grandparents' great big above-ground pool.

19:53.130 --> 20:06.871
It was one of those pools that had an aluminum side and like a vinyl liner, and it had been hastily put up, but it provided hours and hours and hours of fun during the summer, and a space to cool off in the Arizona heat.

20:07.552 --> 20:13.682
Now, on this particular day, I don't remember how old I was, but I was a fairly little kid, maybe

20:13.762 --> 20:15.345
maybe around six years old or so.

20:16.026 --> 20:22.859
And we had been playing around in the pool when my grandfather introduced us to a brand new pool toy.

20:23.219 --> 20:28.129
It was a great big green inflated alligator, a lot like this one here.

20:28.890 --> 20:37.586
Now, what we all decided to do was all the kids pile onto this alligator made for two, now carrying about six different kids.

20:37.666 --> 20:47.924
And one of the adults decided that it would be hilarious to come up underneath the inflatable pool toy and knock all of the kids off into the water.

20:48.505 --> 20:58.322
So I fell right off of the pool toy and into the water, and I don't know what I landed on, but I landed in such a way that all of the air got knocked out of me.

20:58.402 --> 21:03.298
I remember being disoriented and having a hard time figuring out even where I was.

21:03.358 --> 21:06.207
I must have knocked my head in my back or something.

21:06.548 --> 21:10.802
And all of a sudden I realized I didn't have any

21:10.914 --> 21:11.495
oxygen.

21:11.635 --> 21:12.436
I had no air.

21:12.796 --> 21:16.000
I started to panic and try to find my way up and out.

21:16.060 --> 21:25.792
And what was happening is that the people around me, they were still having fun and bouncing around and getting back on the alligator and back off of it and grownups were throwing kids around.

21:25.812 --> 21:30.197
And it sounded like even under the water at that moment, people were having a great time.

21:30.618 --> 21:33.581
But nobody seemed to realize I wasn't there.

21:33.862 --> 21:34.162
Now,

21:34.338 --> 21:41.596
I'm sure this actually was happening in a space of nanoseconds and not the minutes that it felt like to me at the time.

21:42.017 --> 21:43.280
But here's what had happened.

21:43.681 --> 21:52.242
I had gone from a moment of skimming across the surface of the waves on that great, fun toy to suddenly feeling like I was drowning.

21:52.354 --> 22:00.684
I was being kicked and hit and the people who were supposed to notice that I was having trouble didn't and even more so they were making things worse.

22:00.985 --> 22:11.578
I kept getting stepped on and knocked around and I remember as whatever age I was, six or whatever, being there, unable to do anything about the circumstance I was in.

22:12.198 --> 22:20.308
Finally, I got enough strength and kind of pushed myself up as hard as I could and then came headfirst into the bottom of that stupid alligator toy.

22:21.270 --> 22:21.650
I thought,

22:21.922 --> 22:22.403
This is it.

22:23.184 --> 22:24.465
This is how the story ends.

22:25.026 --> 22:26.007
This is my life now.

22:26.508 --> 22:29.031
I was a dramatic six-year-old kid.

22:29.051 --> 22:44.931
Now, what I want you to know is that in just a matter of moments when I thought it was going to be too late and I was seeing stars and starting to panic, the great big strong arms of my grandfather reached into the water, picked me up, and held me out.

22:45.492 --> 22:50.098
I remember the first breath that I took.

22:50.306 --> 22:53.771
being the most rejuvenating thing I had ever experienced.

22:53.831 --> 22:57.336
And I think to this day is the most satisfying breath of air I've ever had.

22:57.656 --> 23:01.602
It was like in that moment things came back to life for me.

23:02.523 --> 23:06.488
Today we're stepping into a series of conversations called rejuvenate.

23:06.629 --> 23:16.402
And it's an invitation for you and for me in a very real sense to take a breath of fresh air, to pause and find ourselves filled up with the goodness of life.

23:16.866 --> 23:26.540
The reason I shared that story at the beginning is because I think a lot of us can relate to that, to moments and spaces and places where things seem to be going great.

23:26.600 --> 23:32.129
We might be having a good time and something happens that knocks us off our sure footing.

23:32.149 --> 23:34.712
And then it feels as though we are drowning.

23:35.233 --> 23:40.401
And what's worse is that the people around us, the people who should notice that something's wrong, they don't.

23:41.042 --> 23:43.826
And they might even make things worse.

23:43.906 --> 23:52.313
We have all experienced that from time to time when it feels as though the stuff of life is crashing over us in waves.

23:52.674 --> 24:11.370
It might be things like the recent pandemic that we've experienced or being overwhelmed at work or at school or as a parent trying to figure out what it looks like to be a single parent or to manage marital crisis and challenge to look at what it means to put food on the table and have time for everybody else and do all of the things that we're being invited into.

24:11.590 --> 24:13.892
And it just feels as though we're stuck

24:13.872 --> 24:19.079
under the waves and we wonder if anybody notices and if anybody's going to help.

24:20.121 --> 24:37.586
I think again we all come into spaces and places moments like that where we just feel like we're drowning and we would give anything for that moment of rescue where we can take a great fresh breath of air and realize that everything's going to be okay.

24:38.370 --> 24:47.474
There's actually a moment in the life and teaching of Jesus, where Jesus is speaking to those who first heard him about some of this very thing.

24:47.554 --> 24:57.426
Because you see, the ministry of Jesus took place in a time and a place where people were overwhelmed because of the waves crashing in over them in all kinds of different ways.

24:57.747 --> 25:02.313
The waves of poverty and oppression and being occupied by a military force.

25:02.613 --> 25:09.842
They were used and abused and they had been waiting for God to do impossible things and it felt like it was never

25:09.890 --> 25:10.471
going to happen.

25:10.672 --> 25:23.537
There were whole groups of people who felt like they had been lost and forgotten and alone, and that the very people who were around them who should have seen that something was wrong and helped them into a different way that they weren't seeing them.

25:23.557 --> 25:25.301
In fact, we're making things worse.

25:26.122 --> 25:31.954
So it's in this kind of context that all of a sudden we see Jesus interacting with the world around him.

25:32.546 --> 25:39.960
In a moment, we're going to read what he has to say, but leading up to that moment, he actually addresses a series of towns around him.

25:40.341 --> 25:44.208
Towns and cities that he says, basically, you're going to have a bad day.

25:44.629 --> 25:48.636
You're going to have a really bad day because the Son of God and Son of Man has come.

25:48.917 --> 25:51.762
The one who is bringing rescue and restoration

25:51.842 --> 25:52.403
has come.

25:52.703 --> 25:55.867
The one who is bringing healing and resurrection has come.

25:56.167 --> 26:06.660
The one who can do miracles, who can position you to find that space, that freshness, that full breath of air, he's come and you've ignored it.

26:06.680 --> 26:07.741
You've cast him aside.

26:08.462 --> 26:19.075
So he addresses each of those places by name and then he steps into a series of conversations or of invitations really that we pick up in Matthew chapter 11.

26:19.676 --> 26:21.298
It says, at that time,

26:22.018 --> 26:30.800
Jesus said, I praise you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and learned and revealed them to little children.

26:31.421 --> 26:34.930
Yes, Father, for this is what you were pleased to do.

26:35.170 --> 26:37.854
All things have been committed to me by my father.

26:38.295 --> 26:40.358
No one knows the son except the father.

26:40.658 --> 26:42.982
And no one knows the father except the son.

26:43.042 --> 26:46.407
And those to whom the son chooses to reveal him.

26:46.427 --> 26:52.376
Jesus is basically saying, hey, when you see me at work, you are seeing God the father.

26:52.416 --> 26:54.519
I'm the image of the invisible God.

26:54.819 --> 27:02.050
You are seeing the one who brings rescue and rest and rest and hope and life and that breath of life.

27:03.092 --> 27:04.594
And so then he says in verse 28,

27:04.770 --> 27:08.959
Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rescue.

27:09.700 --> 27:16.515
Take my yoke upon you and learn from me, for I am gentle and humble in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.

27:17.396 --> 27:20.082
For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.

27:20.834 --> 27:22.116
It's as if in a sense.

27:22.516 --> 27:40.523
Jesus breaks out of the conversation and he says, hey, every single one of you who feels like you're drowning, all of you who feel like you're just getting beat up and there's a lot of pressure to perform and you're wondering if anybody sees you or notices, I see you and I notice you and guess what?

27:41.024 --> 27:46.091
I have come so that you can have a fullness of life and of rest.

27:46.933 --> 27:47.954
In fact, I just,

27:48.034 --> 27:51.599
want you to hear these words spoken over you once more.

27:51.900 --> 28:05.501
In fact, I invite you wherever you are, unless you're driving or something right now, go ahead and close your eyes and listen as these words of Jesus are spoken over you once more.

28:06.723 --> 28:16.818
Come to me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest.

28:18.146 --> 28:28.137
Take my yoke upon you and learn from me, for I am gentle and humble in heart and you will find rest for your souls.

28:29.419 --> 28:33.804
For my yoke is easy and my burden is light.

28:35.526 --> 28:46.578
There's a very real invitation of Jesus from Him for you and to us to step into a space of rejuvenation.

28:47.170 --> 29:00.242
to be truly rejuvenated, not just in a moment, but in a lifestyle where we are full of life, rejuvenated, finding rest for our souls is what Jesus said.

29:02.306 --> 29:07.733
So I wonder, why is it then that so many of us struggle to find that space of rest?

29:07.753 --> 29:23.853
Why is it that so many of us, if Jesus said, hey, come to me, and that's where you will find a kind of soul rest and a lightness of burden, if that's what the promise is, then how come so many of us find ourselves under such constant pressure?

29:24.974 --> 29:29.801
We might feel each day in different circumstances like we're drowning.

29:29.821 --> 29:30.962
I think it's because

29:31.714 --> 29:34.397
We haven't always understood what the invitation is.

29:34.718 --> 29:44.069
So we're gonna spend just a few moments looking at this invitation of Jesus and seeing what it looks like for us to respond and how to receive the fullness of what he's offering here.

29:45.331 --> 29:47.193
So how can we be rejuvenated?

29:47.514 --> 29:48.335
How can we do that?

29:48.635 --> 29:54.583
The first thing that we see in this passage is that we respond to Jesus' sacred invitation.

29:55.263 --> 30:00.530
And his sacred invitation is this, come to me.

30:01.698 --> 30:03.942
come to me is what Jesus said.

30:04.483 --> 30:06.586
And there you will find these things.

30:07.588 --> 30:11.794
You see, an invitation given but not received is worthless.

30:12.115 --> 30:21.630
The invitation, the sacred invitation of Jesus to come to Him only breathes the value in life to us if we accept it and take steps toward Him.

30:22.913 --> 30:26.258
You see, I think it's interesting that Jesus didn't say

30:26.338 --> 30:32.587
come to your echo chamber and kind of spew all of the stuff that's frustrating to them.

30:32.787 --> 30:36.773
He didn't say, come to Netflix and binge watch a season of the office.

30:36.813 --> 30:40.678
He didn't say, come to the bag of Oreos and just like digest that thing.

30:40.718 --> 30:45.044
He didn't say, come to the thing that you do as a coping mechanism.

30:45.284 --> 30:55.058
Now, I'm not saying that any of those things are necessarily bad, but I do think that the invitation of Jesus is to come to Him first.

30:56.066 --> 31:18.034
You see, when Jesus says, come to me and then he says, my yoke is easy and my burden is light and take my yoke upon you, Jesus is actually using language that first century teachers used all the time where it was an invitation, a yoke was an invitation to take on the teaching and the authority and the worldview and the perspective and the purpose of that teacher.

31:18.562 --> 31:25.351
So Jesus, in a sense, is saying, hey, come to me and then follow in the path that I am leading you down.

31:25.651 --> 31:27.053
Come to me first.

31:27.473 --> 31:35.403
Come to me and experience these restful spaces, even as you intersect with the other stuff of life.

31:35.904 --> 31:43.574
Even as you interact and do the things of life that are enjoyable and fun and full of life for you.

31:44.355 --> 31:46.898
Don't run to those things first.

31:48.130 --> 31:49.071
come to me first.

31:49.833 --> 32:03.213
And when you come to me first, then you start to find an order for life, a perspective that helps you understand that no matter what you're facing, no matter what you're going through, no matter what waves are crashing down on you, I have a way.

32:03.313 --> 32:06.137
In fact, Jesus would later say, I am the way.

32:06.798 --> 32:09.302
But there is this space of invitation.

32:09.843 --> 32:17.394
And you and I have to choose whether we'll respond to that or not, to the sacred invitation of Jesus to come to Him.

32:17.954 --> 32:22.200
to submit to Him, to trust Him.

32:24.063 --> 32:32.174
It's not by accident that Jesus interrupts the flow, it seems, of what's happening in the story with these words first come to me.

32:33.916 --> 32:35.599
So how do we find rejuvenation?

32:35.719 --> 32:37.081
How are we rejuvenated?

32:37.121 --> 32:43.250
The first is that we respond to the sacred invitation of Jesus to come to Him.

32:45.613 --> 32:46.354
And then,

32:47.266 --> 32:52.494
And then we see how we're supposed to do that, like the manner in which we're supposed to do that.

32:52.534 --> 32:59.183
Not only do we respond to that sacred invitation come to me, but we respond as a child or as children.

32:59.524 --> 33:03.209
In fact, Jesus unpacks it just a little bit this way.

33:03.269 --> 33:13.164
He says, you have hidden all of these things from the wise and the learned and revealed them to little children.

33:13.965 --> 33:14.546
He is

33:14.786 --> 33:24.018
telling us that in order to really see and understand the invitation of Jesus, we have to look at him with eyes of trust and expectancy.

33:24.194 --> 33:30.362
I'm reminded of the first time that my daughter, Jubilee, received an invitation to a birthday party here in these cities.

33:30.723 --> 33:32.625
And she was so excited.

33:32.666 --> 33:35.149
It was an invitation to a local skating rink.

33:35.389 --> 33:41.478
And I remember her telling me something like, I don't even know how to skate, and I'm so excited.

33:41.798 --> 33:46.464
She could not wait to say yes to this invitation and have a great time.

33:46.504 --> 33:50.270
I don't even know how to skate, I think she said it, but I'm gonna have a great time.

33:50.690 --> 33:53.554
Now, what an incredible perspective.

33:53.666 --> 34:07.769
And it shows me the kind of response that you and I are invited to have as we receive the sacred invitation of Jesus, the sacred invitation to follow Him, to let Him be the one who leads us in the way of rest.

34:08.210 --> 34:10.894
We may not know all that's going to happen.

34:10.994 --> 34:15.762
We may not know all that's going to take place, but we know we can trust

34:17.250 --> 34:27.146
In fact, in the passage of Scripture that we interacted with earlier, Jesus reminds us that He is revealing the Father, that when you've seen Him, you've seen the Father.

34:27.206 --> 34:29.109
And if you've seen the Father, you've seen Him.

34:29.170 --> 34:41.650
And it's this kind of strange back and forth interaction that is a reminder for us that Jesus is a different kind of leader, one that can be wholly trusted.

34:42.306 --> 34:47.691
One that leads us toward the way of life and fullness and, yes, rejuvenation.

34:48.632 --> 35:03.687
When every other system around us would seem to pressure us for more, would seem to demand more from us, Jesus actually invites us, not for what we produce, but for who we are.

35:04.648 --> 35:10.514
And that's what we start to see unpacked and just this quick little interaction with Jesus.

35:11.426 --> 35:20.852
that you and I were made for the kind of soul rest that is found in the leadership of Jesus, in following Jesus.

35:22.176 --> 35:25.746
This is where we find rejuvenation for ourselves.

35:27.170 --> 35:41.578
When Jesus says, my yoke is easy and my burden is light, he's standing in stark contrast with the other systems and teachers of his day, the ones that said basically, you have to work really, really hard in order to please God.

35:41.598 --> 35:47.730
And if you don't do it, then his wrath and his judgment are going to come in spades.

35:48.546 --> 35:52.169
Jesus is saying, I think you've missed some of the invitation there.

35:52.410 --> 35:56.894
And while that may be the system that you're used to, here's what I'm inviting you into.

35:56.914 --> 36:01.699
A space where you are loved and seen and not forgotten.

36:03.000 --> 36:05.362
And you can find rest for your souls.

36:05.482 --> 36:06.904
Yes, there is work to be done.

36:06.964 --> 36:08.145
Yes, there are things to do.

36:08.205 --> 36:15.652
The image of a yoke is actually of a agricultural burden to bear as we do good work together.

36:17.494 --> 36:17.874
But

36:17.954 --> 36:26.556
the kind of pursuit of Jesus that he's inviting us into is, he would say, the place that leads us to rest and rejuvenation.

36:28.100 --> 36:33.874
So when we find ourselves in those spaces where we feel as though we're under constant pressure,

36:34.434 --> 36:39.580
constant pressure to perform, constant pressure to do and be and have more.

36:39.880 --> 36:43.364
The constant pressure to prove our value and our worth.

36:43.724 --> 36:55.057
I hope that when those moments start to creep in for you, that you would hear the voice of Holy Spirit reminding you that Jesus sees you and he loves you as you are.

36:55.497 --> 36:57.460
That you don't have to prove your value to him.

36:57.900 --> 37:03.186
That you're so valuable to him that he died on the cross for you and for me.

37:03.682 --> 37:07.649
There's nothing we can do to earn his love and his favor.

37:08.170 --> 37:12.719
There's nothing we can do to force his hand of purpose in our lives.

37:12.999 --> 37:14.643
We already have his purpose.

37:14.843 --> 37:18.610
We already have his love and his favor.

37:18.630 --> 37:27.186
But you see, one of the things that happens for us, when we don't receive the invitation as a child with hopeful expectation,

37:27.938 --> 37:34.223
we can actually find ourselves trading the sacred space of invitation for the profanity of pressure.

37:34.484 --> 37:35.885
And here's what I mean by that.

37:36.165 --> 37:45.213
It's that when you and I feel like we're living under constant pressure to perform and achieve and do more, it leaks out of us.

37:45.653 --> 37:49.076
And then we start to have those same expectations of others.

37:49.517 --> 37:57.924
And we can in relationship with our kids or our families or those that we have close in connection to, we can start to interact

37:57.904 --> 38:01.188
with them more out of what they produce than who they are.

38:01.408 --> 38:08.637
We can start to interact with them where we apply pressure to them to do more, achieve more, have more, give more.

38:10.219 --> 38:10.840
For what end?

38:10.920 --> 38:11.501
I don't know.

38:14.104 --> 38:19.811
You see, the difference between sacred invitation and profane pressure looks something like this.

38:20.632 --> 38:24.857
